" measures in hydrologic and hydroclimatic model validation (1999) Water Resour Res, 35 (1), pp. 233-241; Loukas, A., Flood frequency estimation by a derived distribution procedure (2002) J Hydrol, 255 (1-4), pp. 69-89; Mehrotra, R., Sharma, A., A nonparametric stochastic downscaling framework for daily rainfall at multiple locations (2006) J Geophys Res, 111. , D15101. doi: 10. 1029/2005JD00637; Metropolis, N., Rosenbluth, A.W., Rosenbluth, M.N., Teller, A.H., Teller, E., Equation of state calculations by fast computing machines (1953) J Chem Phys, 21 (6), pp. 1087-1092; Milly, P.C.D., Wetherald, R.T., Dunne, K.A., Delworth, T.L., Increasing risk of great floods in a changing climate (2002) Nature, 415 (6871), pp. 514-517; Nash, J.E., Sutcliffe, J.V., River flow forecasting through conceptual models part I-a discussion of principles (1970) J Hydrol, 10 (3), pp. 282-290; Pizaro, G., Lall, U., El Nino and floods in the US west: what can we expect? (2002) Eos Trans AGU, 83 (32), pp. 349-352; Rabiner, L.R., A tutorial on hidden Markov models and selected applications in speech recognition (1989) Proc IEEE, 77 (2), pp. 257-286; Rahman, A., Weinmann, P.E., Hoang, T.M.T., Laurenson, E.M., Monte Carlo simulation of flood frequency curves from rainfall (2002) J Hydrol, 256 (3-4), pp. 196-210; Robertson, A.W., Kirshner, S., Smyth, P.J., (2003) Hidden Markov models for modeling daily rainfall occurrence over Brazil., , Technical Report ICS-TR 03-27, Information and Computer Science, University of California, Irvine; Robertson, A.W., Kirshner, S., Smyth, P.J., Downscaling of daily rainfall occurrence over Northeast Brazil using a hidden Markov model (2004) J Clim, 17 (22), pp. 4407-4424; Sankarasubramanian, A., Lall, U., Flood quantiles in a changing climate: seasonal forecasts and causal relations (2003) Water Resour Res, 39 (5), p. 1134. , doi:10.1029/2002WR001593; Viterbi, A.J., Error bounds for convolutional codes and an asymptotically optimum decoding algorithm (1967) IEE